bilingual.source: It is probable that it will rain tomorrow.
It is probable that they will arrive late.
The probable cause of the accident was human error.
bilingual.target: 事故的很可能原因是人为错误。

bilingual.source: She is the probable candidate for the new position.
bilingual.target: 她是新职位的很可能候选人。

bilingual.source: The probable outcome of the match is a win for the home team.
bilingual.target: 比赛的很可能结果是主队获胜。

bilingual.source: I think it's ninety per cent probable.
bilingual.target: 我看这有百分之九十的可能性。

bilingual.source: Is it probable that he will come today?
He was named as the probable successor.
bilingual.target: 他被指定为可能的继承人.

bilingual.source: He is a probable candidate for minister.
bilingual.target: 他是一个有希望的部长候选人。

bilingual.source: It is possible/probable for sb. to do sth.
bilingual.target: 对某人而言，做某事是可能的；

list.abstract: probable，英 [ˈprɒbəbl]，美 [ˈprɑːbəbl]。英文单词，作形容词时，指的是可能发生的；或然的。作名词时，指的是有希望入选的人；可能已被击落的飞机。短语搭配为“probable cause（合理根据）”。例句为“It is probable that the economic situation will deteriorate further.（经济形势可能会进一步恶化。）”。

yingyinNormal.en: Did you prepare the warrant that is the subject of this probable cause hearing? That's the one.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你是不是准备了这次合理依据听证会的搜查令，就这句了。

yingyinNormal.en: Probable cause. Bring him in for questioning. Technically, you have jurisdiction. The vice president?
yingyinNormal.zh: 合理理由，把他找来讯问。严格来说，这事在你辖区之内。美利坚合众国的副总统?

yingyinNormal.en: Worst case scenario, the NTSB lists me as the probable cause. That's immediate retirement. No pension. My life's work gone.
yingyinNormal.zh: 最糟的情形国家运输安全委员会有合理根据定我的罪那就是立即退休，退休金也没了我一生的事业付之一炬。

yingyinNormal.en: Every computer simulation with the exact flight parameters demonstrated that a return to LaGuardia was possible. And not just possible, probable.
yingyinNormal.zh: 每个计算机模拟都使用同样的飞行参数，证明返回拉瓜迪亚机场是可能的，而且不只是可能，是可行的。
